// zoo.js

const empty = _ =>
  new Map
  
const fromString = (s = "") =>
  new Map
    ( s
        .split(", ")
        .map(_ => _.split(" is "))
        .map(([ k, _ ]) => [ k, Number(_) ])
    )
  
const toString = (t = empty()) =>
  Array.from
    ( t.entries()
    , ([ animal, qty ]) => `${animal} is ${qty}` 
    )
    .join(", ")
  
const add = (t = empty(), a = "", q = 0) =>
  t.has(a)
    ? t.set(a, t.get(a) + q)
    : t.set(a, q)

export { add, empty, fromString, toString }

// main.js

  'Dog is 5, Cat is 7, Rabbit is 2'

  toString(add(fromString(input), "Dog", 3))
